<dl id="un4025v"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un4" href="#un4025">UN4: </a>  <a href="../../FF/unbs/un4all.htm#un4025v"> (NLI.5A) 25(v)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> S. Amb. veil in church ~ <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="un4025v"> <li>Ulysses unlocated</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">St. Ambrose does not, indeed, show any deliberate contempt. Woman must be obedient, but not servile, to her husband. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> And when he is asked why she must <mark>veil herself in the churches</mark>, while her husband does not, he answers, because &ldquo;she was not made to the image of God, like man&rdquo;. <small> Joseph McCabe, <a name="JMRW1" href="/udra/udex.htm#JMRW1"><cite title="source">The Religion of Woman</cite></a> (1905), 31</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
